| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | SS 2\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Values Education 2 \n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Foundation of Human Actions\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | VE 2\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Arts, Drafting & Technology 2\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | An Introduction to the Design Process - \nResistant Materials and Electronics (Application & Evaluation)\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | ADTech 2\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Earth Science\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Fundamentals of Earth and Space Science\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | ES\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Physical Education, Health and Music 2\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" |\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | PEHM 2\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Physical Education 2 \n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Physical Fitness and Basic Movement Education 8 \n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | PE 2\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Health Education 2\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | ME and my FRIENDS: Preventive Drug Education, Safety and First Aid\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | Health 2\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Music 2\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Asian/African Music\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | Music 2\n|}\n\n====Grade 9 (Chemical Elements)====\n*'''[[Lithium]]'''\n*'''[[Potassium]]'''\n*'''[[Sodium]]'''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable collapsible collapsed\"\n|-\n! Subject\n! Title\n! Code\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Biology 1\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Fundamentals of Biology 1\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | Bio 1\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Chemistry 1\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | General Inorganic Chemistry\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | Chem 1\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Physics 1\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Fundamental Physics\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | Phy 1\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Mathematics 3A\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Mathematics 3A\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | Math 3A\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Computer Science 3\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Client-Side Web Development\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | CS 3\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | English 3\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Communication Arts 3 and English & American Literature\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | Eng 3\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Filipino 3\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Retorika, Pagsusuri, at Pagpapahalagang Pampanitikian\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | Fil 3\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Social Science 3\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | World History 2\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | SS 3\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Physical Education, Health and Music 3\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" |\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | PEHM 3\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Physical Education 3\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Group Oriented Activities in Sports and Leisure Education 1\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | PE 3\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Health Education 3\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | My Family and Me: Family Health and Disease Prevention and Control\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | Health 3\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Music 3\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | History and Characteristics of Western Music\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | Music 3\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Mathematics 3B\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Statistics and Probability \n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | Math 3B\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Earth Science \n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Fundamentals of Earth and Space Science\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | ES \n|}\n\n====Grade 10 (Subatomic Particles)====\n*'''[[Electron]]'''\n*'''[[Proton]]'''\n*'''[[Neutron]]'''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable collapsible collapsed\"\n|-\n! Subject\n! Title\n! Code\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Biology 2\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Fundamentals of Biology 2 \n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | Bio 2\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Chemistry 2\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Introduction to Organic Chemistry / General Inorganic Chemistry 2\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | Chem 2\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Physics 2\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Fundamental Physics 2\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | Phy 2\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Mathematics 4\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Mathematics 4\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | Math 4\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Computer Science 4\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Object-Oriented Programming \n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | CS 4\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | English 4\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Communication Arts 4 and World Literature\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | Eng 4\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Filipino 4\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Kasaysayan at Pag-unlad ng Panitikang Pilipino \n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | Fil 4\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Social Science 4\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Philippine Government & Politics / Constitution \n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | SS 4\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Physical Education, Health and Music 4\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" |\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | PEHM 4\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Physical Education 4\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Group Oriented Activities in Sports and Leisure Education 2\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | PE 4\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Health Education 4\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | My Society and Me\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | Health 4\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Music 4\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Popular Music and Music Performance \n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | Music 4\n|-\n! style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" | Research 1\n| style=\"background:#98FB98;\" | Science, Technology, Engineering, and Mathematics (STEM) Research 1\n| style=\"background:#FBF373;\" | Res 1\n|-\n|}\n\n===Academic Grading System===\nGrades are reported in terms of the stanine. 1.00 is the highest grade while 5.00 is a failing mark. 2.50 is the passing grade and any grade lower than this is termed ''substandard''. The student's current standing for a subject is calculated by adding 1/3 of the previous quarter's grade and 2/3 of the tentative grade of the quarter. The general weighted average (GWA) of the student should be 2.25 or better to be in good standing.\n\n====Stanine====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Grade\n! Percentage Range\n! Equivalent Range\n! Description\n|-\n! style=\"background:#6cf;\"| 1.00\n| style=\"background:#ACE3FF\" | 96 - 100\n| style=\"background:#BDE9FF\" | 98 - 100\n| style=\"background:#D1F0FF\" | Excellent\n|-\n! style=\"background:#6cf;\"| 1.25\n| style=\"background:#ACE3FF\" | 90 - 95\n| style=\"background:#BDE9FF\" | 95 - 97\n| style=\"background:#D1F0FF\" | Very Good\n|-\n! style=\"background:#6cf;\"| 1.50\n| style=\"background:#ACE3FF\" | 84 - 89 \n| style=\"background:#BDE9FF\" | 92 - 94\n| style=\"background:#D1F0FF\" | Very Good\n|-\n! style=\"background:#3f3;\"| 1.75\n| style=\"background:#6CFF6C\" | 78 - 83\n| style=\"background:#89FF89\" | 89 - 91\n| style=\"background:#A1FFA1\" | Good\n|-\n! style=\"background:#3f3;\"| 2.00\n| style=\"background:#6CFF6C\" | 72 - 77\n| style=\"background:#89FF89\" | 86 - 88\n| style=\"background:#A1FFA1\" | Good\n|-\n! style=\"background:#3f3;\"| 2.25\n| style=\"background:#6CFF6C\" | 66 - 71\n| style=\"background:#89FF89\" | 83 - 85\n| style=\"background:#A1FFA1\" | Satisfactory\n|-\n! style=\"background:#3f3;\"| 2.50\n| style=\"background:#6CFF6C\" | 60 - 65\n| style=\"background:#89FF89\" | 80 - 82\n| style=\"background:#A1FFA1\" | Satisfactory\n|-\n! style=\"background:#FFAE19\" | 2.75\n| style=\"background:#FFBE47\" | 55 - 59\n| style=\"background:#FFC459\" | 77 - 79\n| style=\"background:#FFD07A\" | Unsatisfactory\n|-\n! style=\"background:#FFAE19\" | 3.00\n| style=\"background:#FFBE47\" | 50 - 54\n| style=\"background:#FFC459\" | 74 - 76\n| style=\"background:#FFD07A\" | Unsatisfactory\n|-\n! style=\"background:#FFAE19\" | 4.00\n| style=\"background:#FFBE47\" | 40 - 49\n| style=\"background:#FFC459\" | 70 - 73\n| style=\"background:#FFD07A\" | Conditional Failure\n|-\n! style=\"background:#FF2A2A\" | 5.00\n| style=\"background:#FF4141\" | Below 40\n| style=\"background:#FE5353\" | Below 70\n| style=\"background:#FF6E6E\"| Failed\n|}\nNote: The percentage range is used in actual computations of grades while the equivalent range is used in translating the grades for use outside of the system (e.g. application to colleges/universities).\n\n===Director's List===\nEvery quarter, students who garner a general weighted average (GWA) of 1.50 or better are included in an honor roll known as the '''Director's List'''.\n\n==Student life==\n===The Student Alliance===\nThe Student Alliance (SA) is the highest governing body of the entire studentry.\n\n===Pisay's Researchers in Science and Mathematics (''PRISM'')===\nThe Pisay\u2019s Researchers in Science and Mathematics is the premier science institution of the Philippine Science High School - SOCCSKSARGEN Region Campus. It was first established by the PSHS-SRC pioneering batch of 2019 to help support and facilitate scholars\u2019 activities related to Science, Technology, Engineering and Mathematics, which also helps PSHS-SRC in promoting STEM inside and outside the campus.\n\nPRISM is headed by scholars elected from the student body to primarily organize the said activities. Any scholar who meets the eligibility requirements stipulated in the PRISM Constitution-and-by-Laws are automatically nominated to take an officership position under PRISM.\n\n===Alternative Learning Activities (ALA)===\n\n* '''Young Inventors' Club'''\n* '''The Environmentalists' Club'''\n* '''Sports Club'''\n* '''Book Lovers' Club'''\n* '''Art Club'''\n* '''Public Speakers' Guild'''\n* '''Math Club'''\n* '''Weave Club'''\n* '''Performing Arts Club''' (Music, Dance, Theatre Club)\n\n===The Tunog System===\nIn order to develop the bond and unity among scholars, the PSHS-SRC implemented the 'Tunog' System which is set to anchor any school activity this school year 2014-2015. The implementation of this system aims for six (6) aspects: Academic mentoring; Peer counseling to provide emotional support; Monitoring of overall student performances; Sports events for leisure and physical fitness; Musical, theatrical and cultural events and promotion; and, Maintenance of cleanliness and orderliness.\n\nThe system consists of six tunog which includes:\n# Debakandabest\n# Agong\n# Kudyapi\n# Gangza\n# Kulintang\n# Kubing'''\nEach tunog is composed of members from the students, faculty, and staff led by the Datu, Wai\u00edr and Raja Tagasulat. The names were derived from the balangay system of the first settlers in the Philippines to reflect patriotism in the Filipinos' cultural ways and to live out the core values of the Philippine Science High School System. \"The main purposes of the tunog system are to enhance the social interaction between the teachers and the students of different grade levels and to help every student in each tunog with their academic studies. I hope that it will fully prosper for years and will effectively serve its purpose,\" said Jhona Cresila Quezada, the schools' Student Services Division chief.<ref>Fornan, Glydel. (2014, June\u2013November). Tunog System rings for scholars. Pisay Scholar, p. A2.</ref>\n\nSince School Year 2016-2017, the Tunog System is no longer being used. The penultimate of the capabilities of the scholars are limitless.\n\n===School Publications===\n\nThe school annually produces two publications that allows the scholars the optimum opportunity to express their thoughts and opinions freely. '''THE TWELFTH QUILL''' is the PSHS-SRC's official publication in English. '''PISAY PLUMA''', on the other hand, is the official publication in Filipino. Both publications provide a good training ground for scholars in the field of journalism as reporting, layout, design, editing, and final production are done by the students under the supervision of a faculty adviser.\n\n===Science and Humanities & Sports Festival===\n\nThe school annually holds its own version of intramural named '''''Science and Humanities & Sports Festival'''''. The said event is an event where all students get to finally showcase their talents, skills, and abilities. The reigning champion of the event is Batch 2020, the present Grade 10.\n\n==Student Services and Facilities==\nAs true to its mission and vision, the campus is also equipped with certain facilities to provide its scholars the welfare and development they need when they are in school.\n\n===Residence Halls===\nThere are two dormitories in the vicinity of the campus, namely Girls\u2019 Residence Hall and Boys' Residence Hall. These dormitories offer accommodations for the nation\u2019s scholars from all over SOCCSKSARGEN and some neighboring areas.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mc.pshs.edu.ph/campus-life/student-services/dormitories/|title=Residence Halls}}</ref>\n\n===Library===\n===Guidance Center===\n===Clinic=== \nPSHS-SRC has its own clinic where students can go  if they have injuries, medical concerns, or if they need medicine. Student's health records are also kept in the clinic. The \"pisay\" smc clinic also has a nurse to help students when they need assistance.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Philippine Science High Schools}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:SOCCSKSARGEN Region Campus}}\n[[Category:Philippine Science High School System]]\n[[Category:Schools in South Cotabato]]\n[[Category:Education in Koronadal]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toNarra(link changed toPterocarpus) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page":