{"title_page": "Margus Lepa", "text_new": "{{Expand language|topic=|langcode=Et|otherarticle=Margus Lepa|date=April 2020}}\n{{BLP sources|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name            = Margus Lepa\n| image           = T\u00f5nu_Alveus_ja_Margus_Lepa_92.jpg\n| imagesize       =\n| alt             =\n| caption         = T\u00f5nu Alveus and Margus Lepa (1992)\n| birth_name       =\n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|1953|10|7|df=yes}}<br>{{Citation needed|date=September 2010}}\n| birth_place      = [[Pelgulinn]], [[Tallinn]], [[Estonia]]<br>{{Citation needed|date=September 2010}}\n| death_date       = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} Death date then birth -->\n| death_place      =\n| othername       =\n| occupation      = [[Actor]] <!--\"and [[comedian]]\" - hidden at September 2010 - no mention, with/without attribution, in prose-->\n| yearsactive     = Since 1970<ref name=imdbtype>[[Database]] (undated). [https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0503191/filmotype \"Filmography by Type for Margus Lepa\"].  ''[[Internet Movie Database|The Internet Movie Database]]''.  Accessed 1 September 2010.</ref>\n| spouse          =\n| partner =\n| website         =\n}}\n\n'''Margus Lepa''' (born 7 October 1953){{Citation needed|date=September 2010}} is an [[Estonia]]n radio journalist<!--, [[comedian]] - hidden at September 2010 - no mention, with/without attribution, in prose--> and former actor.\n\n==Early life and education==\nHe was born in [[Pelgulinn]], a subdistrict of [[Tallinn]], [[Estonia]] to baritone Harry Vilpat and actress [[Astrid Lepa]].\n{{Expand section|date=September 2010|prose on parents, education, etc}}\n\n==Career==\n===Film acting===\nBetween 1970 and 2020, Lepa portrayed the character of Georg Aadniel Kiir in the films  ''[[Spring (1969 film)|Kevade]]'' (Spring) (1970), ''[[Suvi (film)|Suvi]]'' (Summer) (1976) ''[[S\u00fcgis (film)|S\u00fcgis]]'' (Autumn) (1991), and ''Talve'' (Winter) (2020), all directed by [[Arvo Kruusement]], apart from ''Talve'', and based on a series of novels by [[Oskar Luts]].\n\n'''Filmography'''\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Genre\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|1970 || ''[[Kevade]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://elu.ohtuleht.ee/463110/margus-lepa-rahvuslus-on-mingisugune-vaimuhaigus|title=Margus Lepa: \"Rahvuslus on mingisugune vaimuhaigus!\" {{!}} Elu|website=elu.ohtuleht.ee|language=et|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>||[[drama film|drama]] || Kiir ||\n|-\n|1976 || ''[[Suvi (film)|Suvi]]'' ||[[comedy-drama]] ||  Kiir ||\n|-\n|1991 || ''[[S\u00fcgis]]'' || [[comedy-drama]] || Kiir ||\n|-\n|2020 || ''[[Talve (film)|Talve]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.delfi.ee/a/88603915|title=Margus Lepa j\u00e4i p\u00e4rast lahutust \u00fcksi poega kasvatama: mu naine tegi v\u00e4ga \u00f5igesti. N\u00fc\u00fcdseks on ta ostnud Hispaaniasse maja|date=1578578455|website=Kroonika|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://menu.err.ee/1009041/margus-lepa-kiire-rollist-filmis-talve-mul-oli-moraalne-kohustus|title=Margus Lepa Kiire rollist filmis \"Talve\": mul oli moraalne kohustus|last=ERR|date=2019-12-02|website=ERR|language=et|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>||[[comedy-drama]] || Kiir ||\n|-\n|}\n\n===Radio acting===\nFor many years, he performed, together with [[Raimo Aas]], in ''[[Meelejahutaja]]''., a Sunday morning [[radio]] programme.{{Citation needed|date=September 2010|reason=also, clarify...what type of radio acting?   is this where the \"comedian\" occupation enters?  no wiki article on the program yet and wiki article on Aas is unclear as well.}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|0503191}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2011}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lepa, Margus}}\n[[Category:1953 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Estonian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Estonian male radio actors]]\n[[Category:20th-century Estonian male actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Tallinn]]\n[[Category